ent classifier configuration obtained\nat the method-level can also be used at the file-level (and vice versa).\nConclusion: Our results lead us to conclude that configuration has a large\nimpact on both the top-k performance and the required effort for method-level\nbug localization, suggesting that the IR-based configuration settings should be\ncarefully selected and the required effort metric should be included in future\nbug localization studies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Jun 2018 13:43:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-21"}
